Russians warn of fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters who replace the bank’s phone number has increased.
This is reported by the Kommersant with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator transmitted information about more than 2.5 thousand numbers to customers of various financial organizations.
In 189 cases, the operators found a replacement of the number.
Another 218 rooms were blocked, and in 59 cases, restrictions were imposed on the use of financial services.
Deputy Head of the Information Security Department of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that the replacement of the number was encountered by a wide range of Russian banks.
He explained that operators do not always respond to the Central Bank’s warnings about fraudulent calls, referring to the lack of such an obligation in the “On Communications” law.
In the bank "Open", Rosbank and Alpha-bank confirmed information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the replacement of the number.
As reported in the press service "Bilina", part of the information about the fraudulent calls sent by the central bank was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are actually used by banks to communicate with customers.
Blocking them would lead to failures in the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of fraudsters’ numbers, which the telecommunications operator will contact at each call to check the number.
He explained that the establishment of such a base would require amendments to the legislation.
