The supply of "sanctions" to Russia fell 100 times
The Russian government estimated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from countries subject to the Russian food embargo has decreased more than 100 times since 2013.
According to a report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand tons of products were imported from sanctions countries versus 3 million 442.2 thousand tons for the same period of 2013, reports Interfax.
At the same time, the value of imported products decreased to <0x24>226.5 million from <0x24>4 billion to <0x24>975.5 million, respectively.
It is about the supply of goods that have not fallen under the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the decline in import-prohibited products was offset by an increase in imports from CIS countries, Africa, Southeast Asia and Serbia.
At the end of August, the government extended until 31 December 2020 the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and foodstuffs, which are prohibited from importing into Russia under counter-sanctions.
The document, posted on the official legal information portal, noted that the rules have been extended for another year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the sanctions were imposed on products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, since August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein, and since January 1, 2016 - Ukraine have "joined" this list.
Putin’s decree on the destruction of illegally imported “sanctions” (products covered by the food embargo that Moscow introduced in response to anti-Russian Western sanctions) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government has allowed to destroy “sanctional” food in any lawful way.
As the Western sanctions continued, the Russian Federation also extended its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, the measure does not apply to products that citizens import for personal use.
The ban does not apply to the importation of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Council under the President of the Russian Federation for the development of civil society and human rights Mikhail Fedotov previously called the destruction of food “just immoral”, and this, he said, negatively affects the education of people.
In addition, with the initiative to prohibit the destruction of foods suitable for consumption, Rospotrebnadzor spoke in early June.
After that, a similar recommendation was made to the Government by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And the deputy prime minister of the Russian Federation Alexei Gordeev said that the destruction of food products is wrong, and it is necessary to think about how to use them as intended, assessing the quality.
The head of the firm is found guilty of evasion of taxes
The verdict of the Lenin district court of the city of Cheboksary is a violation of the order of the director of the company "Earth and Law" and Vyacheslav Morozov is found guilty of the offences provided for in article 2 "b" of the law of the Russian Federation.
This is reported by the press service of the investigative management of the SCR on Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov included information on incomplete transactions in the tax records of LLC.
According to fictitious documents, the company incurred additional costs and, therefore, the amounts of taxes payable on value added and on the profits of the organization were reduced.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years in prison on parole.
