This is reported by TASS with reference to the press service of the European Southern Observatory (ESO).
According to ESO, construction of the dome has officially begun this week, where the E-ELT (European Extremely Large Telescope) will be located, while the most expensive and ambitious ground-based astronomical project.
Its total cost, according to ESO, will exceed <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>1 billion.
Much of this money will be spent on the manufacture of equipment and the construction of the observatory building.
The most expensive and complex component of the telescope is its record-breaking large mirror, whose diameter will be about 39 meters.
It will be assembled from 798 hexagonal segments measuring 1.4 meters.
This huge mirror, as well as two auxiliary reflective surfaces with a diameter of 4.2 and 3.75 meters, will help E-ELT get the first detailed photographs of planets outside the solar system, stars in other galaxies, as well as looking for Earth’s twins.
In addition, scientists will try to use this observatory to observe the surrounding Sgr A*, a supermassive black hole in the center of the Milky Way.
Despite the fact that the construction of the dome has only begun, mirrors, scientific tools and other components of the observatory have been developing scientists, engineers and other specialists for three years - since the announcement of the first plans for the construction of the E-ELT.
